### English Title:
US Stocks Reduce Losses Amid Trade Agreement Hopes

### English Text Summary:
US stocks eased their losses on Monday as investors clung to hopes that President Donald Trump might shift from imposing tariffs to negotiating trade agreements. The S&P 500 index closed down about 0.2%, following a volatile trading day marked by significant fluctuations. Despite Trump's escalating threats of tariffs on China, he indicated that negotiations with Japan and other countries were forthcoming. The article highlights the severe impact of tariffs on global economies, with analysts warning of potential destructive effects if world leaders fail to reach an agreement. The market experienced sharp declines, with the S&P 500 dropping over 10% in three days, reflecting widespread concerns about the economic implications of tariffs.

